==Old English==
===Etymology===
Common Germanic *''[[hwe(g)ulo]]'' from a Proto-Indo-European root *''[[qwel-]]'' ''going around''.
Cognate with:
* Old Norse ''hvél'', ''[[hjól]]''
* Danish ''[[hjul]]''
* Dutch ''[[wiel]]''
* Common Slavic *''[[kolo]]''
* Latin [[colere]] (''to cultivate, inhabit'' = ''turn around'')
===Noun===
'''hwēol''', '''hwēogol'''

# [[wheel]]

